claim.claim-text:
A method for controlling a display apparatus, comprising:
separating a received image into a left-eye image and a right-eye image and processing the left-eye image and the right-eye image;
outputting the left-eye image and the right-eye image alternatingly;
calculating a pixel value difference between the left-eye image and the right-eye image based on units relating to pixels that constitute the left-eye image and the right-eye image;
detecting a crosstalk generating area by using the calculated pixel value difference and a preset response speed of a display panel; and
displaying the detected crosstalk generating area distinguishably with respect to at least one other area.
